# Reference
https://docs.python.org/2/library/os.path.html
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/82831/how-to-check-whether-a-file-exists


import os
os.path.exists(path)
Return True if path refers to an existing path.
Returns False for broken symbolic links.
On some platforms, this function may return False if permission is not granted to execute os.stat() on the requested file,
even if the path physically exists.

os.path.exists(file_path)
This returns True for both files and directories but you can instead use os.path.isfile to test if it's a file specifically. 
It follows symlinks.



